The first distinct PN choice exposed a small residual cross-correlation edge at one equal-power frequency point (14/200 displaced locks), so I tightened the construction to the reviewer’s natural seed separation (`reference_seed XOR 0x5555`) and added a regression test covering all 1,800 co-channel trials. That test now proves there are no centroid/other locks. Because the code changed after the first full run, I’m rerunning the complete release campaign rather than splicing results.
